## Seat utilization recovery windows matter before renewal

Subscriptions with temporary utilization dips often recovered when intervention
occurred more than 60 days before renewal.

Fact: Early intervention correlated with utilization recovery in low-utilization subscriptions.
Belief: Timing of renewal preparation is a stronger lever than static utilization thresholds.
Value: Renewal strategy should favor proactive value recovery over late discounting.
Precedent: Last-cycle save motions succeeded when initiated before the final 60-day window.
